[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":440},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fgulp\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fgulp-series-18-pug-jade\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fgulp\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fgulp-series-18-pug-jade\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fgulp\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fgulp-series-18-pug-jade\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fgulp\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fgulp-series-18-pug-jade\u002F":416,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fgulp\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fgulp-series-18-pug-jade\u002F":425},"\u002Fgulp\u002F20190613\u002F2790703784\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":397,"date":398,"description":399,"extension":400,"lang":401,"meta":402,"navigation":403,"path":404,"readingMinutes":405,"seo":406,"standalone":407,"stem":408,"tags":409,"tldr":413,"updated":413,"url":414,"__hash__":415},"content\u002Fen\u002FGulp\u002Fgulp-series-18-pug-jade.md","Gulp Series Bonus: Adding pug\u002Fjade","3784279070",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":391},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,37,50,59,65,68,79,82,90,97,104,108,111,143,147,156,273,282,288,291,343,346,352,359,369,375,382,387],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Bonus chapter — for people who use pug\u002Fjade (myself included). pug is a template language that simplifies HTML. Knowing more templating languages is good for a frontend dev — you type less. This won't be pushed to the GitHub repo since not everyone uses pug\u002Fjade.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"pugjade","pug\u002Fjade",[17,25,26],{},"Quick primer first — pug used to be called jade. The name was changed due to some legal\u002Ftrademark issues.",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"From the web","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FS1AQnOH.png",[17,35,36],{},"Why use pug?",[38,39,40,44,47],"ul",{},[41,42,43],"li",{},"Simplified syntax",[41,45,46],{},"HTML modularization (won't cover how to write pug in this post — just install)",[41,48,49],{},"Has some programming\u002Fexpression capabilities",[17,51,52,53,58],{},"One of my projects — ",[54,55,57],"a",{"href":56},"\u002FPug-Sweetaste\u002F","Sweetaste (dessert e-commerce)"," — uses pug. The HTML looks like:",[17,60,61],{},[30,62],{"alt":63,"src":64},"pug","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F4d24U6i.png",[17,66,67],{},"Looks great, but there are downsides:",[38,69,70,73,76],{},[41,71,72],{},"Copying someone else's HTML structure requires conversion first",[41,74,75],{},"Indentation can be a pain",[41,77,78],{},"Strict syntax",[17,80,81],{},"The first downside hits me often — I use Bootstrap 4 a lot, and Bootstrap 4 examples are all plain HTML, so I have to convert to pug before pasting. Trade-offs everywhere. Useful resources:",[17,83,84],{},[54,85,89],{"href":86,"rel":87},"https:\u002F\u002Fpugjs.org\u002Fapi\u002Fgetting-started.html",[88],"nofollow","pug official site",[17,91,92],{},[54,93,96],{"href":94,"rel":95},"https:\u002F\u002Fhtml2jade.org\u002F",[88],"HTML to pug",[17,98,99],{},[54,100,103],{"href":101,"rel":102},"https:\u002F\u002Fpughtml.com\u002F",[88],"pug to HTML",[12,105,107],{"id":106},"setup","Setup",[17,109,110],{},"Install — Gulp has an official pug plugin:",[112,113,118],"pre",{"className":114,"code":115,"language":116,"meta":117,"style":117},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","npm install --save gulp-pug\n","js","",[119,120,121],"code",{"__ignoreMap":117},[122,123,126,130,134,137,140],"span",{"class":124,"line":125},"line",1,[122,127,129],{"class":128},"sMAXC","npm install ",[122,131,133],{"class":132},"sWyjQ","--",[122,135,136],{"class":128},"save gulp",[122,138,139],{"class":132},"-",[122,141,142],{"class":128},"pug\n",[12,144,146],{"id":145},"how-to-use","How to use",[17,148,149,150,155],{},"Per the ",[54,151,154],{"href":152,"rel":153},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.npmjs.com\u002Fpackage\u002Fgulp-pug",[88],"official docs",":",[112,157,159],{"className":114,"code":158,"language":116,"meta":117,"style":117},"gulp.task('pug', () => {\n  return gulp.src('.\u002